snippet: Andrew Fryberg, 15, died of wounds sustained when his cousin, a freshman at Marysville-Pilchuck High School, opened fire in the cafeteria two weeks ago.
abstract: Fifteen-year-old Andrew Fryberg dies of wounds sustained in shooting at Marysville-Pilchuck High School in Washington State, making him fifth teenager to die as result of incident; was cousin of shooter Jaylen Fryberg.
lead_paragraph: Andrew Fryberg, 15, died of wounds sustained when his cousin, a freshman at Marysville-Pilchuck High School, opened fire in the cafeteria two weeks ago.

headline.main: Death Toll Rises to 5 in School Shooting
